The [[Abyssal Sire]] is a level 350 [[Slayer]] boss that can only be killed when assigned [[Abyssal demon]]s or the Sire itself with the required [[Slayer]] level of 85.

It is mainly killed for its [[unsired]] drops, which can be used at the [[Font of Consumption]] to obtain valuable rewards such as the [[abyssal dagger]], parts of the [[abyssal bludgeon]], or the [[abyssal orphan]] [[pet]].

Note that while the Sire is a solo boss, some of its attacks '''can''' hit other players that happen to be nearby. If using spellbook swap for thralls, only the melee thrall works for Phase 2 but any thrall works for Phase 3.

==Requirements==
*{{SCP|Slayer|85}} with an [[Abyssal demon]] slayer task
*Access to [[Fairy rings]] or partial completion of the [[Enter the Abyss]] miniquest to access the [[Abyssal Nexus]]

===Recommendations===
*High combat stats. Although not required, see the skill levels below for an indication of the advised stats:
*{{SCP|Attack|90}} or higher
*{{SCP|Strength|90}} or higher
*{{SCP|Defence|90}} or higher
*{{SCP|Ranged|90}} or higher
*{{SCP|Hitpoints|90}} or higher
*{{SCP|Magic|92}} or higher
*{{SCP|Prayer|70+}} for [[Piety]]

==Transportation==
The Sire is located in the [[Abyssal Nexus]], which can be easily accessed by fairy ring code {{Fairycode|DIP}}. Players without partial completion of [[Fairytale II - Cure a Queen]] will instead have to enter the [[Abyss]] via the [[Mage of Zamorak]] and go through the one-way passage on the south side. This requires running briefly through the [[Wilderness]], [[Skull (status)|Skulling]], and will drain all of your prayer points so it is not recommended.

There are four Sires in each world, in the north-east, north-west, south-east and south-western areas of the Nexus. There are four [[Eye (Abyssal Nexus)|eyes]] near the Font of Consumption; interacting with them will tell you if there is another player in that chamber.

==Mechanics==
===Respiratory systems, tentacles, and stunning===
During Phase 1 the player will need to kill all four [[respiratory system]]s. They are protected by six immobile [[Tentacle (Abyssal Sire)|tentacles]] which, when active, prevent almost all damage to the respiratory systems and attack nearby players for up to 30 damage (reduced slightly by Protect from Melee). Players will always hit at least 50% of their weapon's maximum hit on the respiratory systems, meaning all four can be taken down in 2 attacks each with a non-demonbane weapon that has a max hit of at least 50, assuming the player does not miss either attack.

The Sire and its tentacles can be stunned for 30 seconds by one of the following methods, leaving the respiratory systems open to attack:
*Deal 75 damage to the Sire with ranged/magic
*Cast a [[Shadow spells|Shadow spell]] on the Sire (effect applies even if it splashes):
**[[Shadow Rush]]: 25% chance to stun
**[[Shadow Burst]]: 50% chance to stun
**[[Shadow Blitz]]: 75% chance to stun
**[[Shadow Barrage]]: 100% chance to stun
The tentacles are inactive during Phase 2 but become active again in Phase 3.

The fastest way to handle Phase 1 is to attack the Sire with any ranged or magic weapon/spell that is not a shadow spell to wake it up, then manually cast Shadow Barrage on the Sire to stun it for 27 seconds. This allows you to begin attacking the 4 respiratory vents around the edge of the room instantly. While it is possible to initiate the fight by casting Shadow Barrage on an inactive Sire, the stun will not be applied for 10 game ticks after being cast (due to the Sire having to perform its waking up animation before the stun applies), meaning a player who does this may be attacked by the tentacles if they move in to kill the respiratory systems too fast.

Using the scorching bow with any arrow type will 1 shot kill all respiratory vents on a successful hit. Simply just click, wait for the experience drop and then click the next one. You do not need to use any prayer during stage 1 if using Shadow Barrage and the scorching bow.

===Standard attacks===
During phase 2, the Sire uses three types of melee attacks; a swipe from its right arm, a flick from its right tendril, or a flick from both tendrils. The double flick can deal up to 66 damage. Using [[Protect from Melee]] will reduce the damage from these attacks to 6, 6 and 26 respectively.

===Miasma Pools===
[[File:Sire poisonous fumes.gif|frame|left|The poisonous fumes that players must avoid.]]
In all phases of the fight (though it won't be used in Phase 1 if stunning correctly), the Sire can summon a pool of miasma under the player's position. The pool causes damage in a 3x3 area, dealing 10-30 poison damage per tick if on the central tile or 2-8 per tick on the outer tiles. This damage cannot be mitigated by any type of poison protection, and can also poison the player starting at 8 damage. There is enough time upon seeing the pool appear to avoid all damage by running 2 tiles away.

In Phases 1 and 2 the attack is indicated by the Sire clenching both its claws towards its stomach, along with a dark-green spiral energy appearing above it. There is no animation for the attack in Phase 3.

After the Sire explodes in Phase 3, it uses this attack a minimum of three more times then stops if all 15 minions are alive.

===Minions===
In all phases of the fight the Sire can create [[Spawn|spawns]]. They randomly attack with ranged for up to 9 damage and melee for up to 4. They have 15 hitpoints and low accuracy.

If the spawn is not killed within 15 seconds, it will mature into a [[scion]], which has 60 hitpoints and has higher accuracy. They randomly attack with ranged for up to 16 damage and melee for up to 10. Therefore, when many minions are present, [[Protect from Missiles]] is recommended, as their ranged attacks are more accurate and damaging. 

Demonbane attacks will always land as [[successful hit]]s against them regardless of the player's bonuses.

Minions can be killed with [[barrage spells]] or [[Chinchompa (weapon)|chinchompas]] due to their low Defence, however they are not required to be killed for the fight. Once the Sire is killed, all minions will die alongside it.

