===Forced Teleport and Explosion===
During Phase 2, if the player attempts to safespot the Sire, it will forcibly teleport them next to it before discharging a blast of energy from the portal in its stomach, dealing up to 60 damage if the player doesn't run away in time.

During Phase 3, when the Sire goes under 140 health, it will teleport the player next to itself and trigger a highly damaging explosion; the damage can be avoided by running directly away from the Sire as soon as the player is teleported.

==Strategy==
'''Note:''' Make sure that [[Auto Retaliate]] is off when killing the Sire.
{{Tile markers box|Module:Tile markers/Abyssal Sire.json}}
===Phase 1===
The Sire wakes up and begins the fight when attacked. If not stunned, it will summon miasma pools under the player and create spawns. The six [[Tentacle (Abyssal Sire)|tentacles]] will also awaken. These tentacles are static, but attack with typeless crush that can deal up to 30 damage, slightly reduced with [[Protect from Melee]].

The player needs to kill all four [[Respiratory system|respiratory systems]] to progress. However, with the Sire awake, the tentacles will protect the respiratory systems from attacks, and any attacks dealt to them while the boss is awake will be reduced to 0-3 damage regardless of the experience drop given.

In order to remove the protection provided by the tentacles, the Sire must be disoriented. This can be done in one of two ways; dealing 75 damage with ranged or magic (as the boss is not accessible with melee), or using a [[shadow spells|shadow spell]] against it. Shadow spells, if they successfully disorient the Sire, will do so for 30 seconds. The chance of this occurring is dependent on the tier of shadow spell; [[Shadow Rush]] has a 25% chance, [[Shadow Burst]] 50%, [[Shadow Blitz]] 75% and [[Shadow Barrage]] guarantees it. '''While casting a shadow spell on an inactive Sire will both wake it up and potentially stun it, the stun from this spell will not be applied for 10 game ticks after being cast. A shadow spell cast on an awoken Sire will be applied instantly.'''

When stunned, the respiratory systems should be killed with ranged or magic, depending on what the player prefers. Upon a [[successful hit]], demonbane weapons and spells will destroy them instantly regardless of the player's bonuses. It is highly recommended players bring a [[scorching bow]] and [[bronze arrow]]s, since these are cheap and readily available, and the bow has high accuracy even when not bringing ranged armour switches.

If a non-demonbane weapon is used, the player will deal anywhere from 50%-100% of their maximum hit as damage. Bringing a weapon that has a max hit of 50 or higher will be sufficient enough to destroy the respiratory systems in two hits.

Within 30 seconds, the player will be easily able to destroy all of the respiratory systems in one cycle with demonbane. Without demonbane, it is possible to do so if they can be two hit; three hits will likely require a second stun. Despite the 30 second stun timer, it is actually 27 seconds, as the tentacles will awaken at this mark and immediately protect the systems.

[[File:Sire tile markers.png|alt=Image showing tiles useful for fighting Sire|thumb|In Phase 2 stand on Row 1. When the Sire walks to the centre of the room at the start of Phase 3, run to Row 2. To avoid the explosion attack, run to Row 3 immediately after you are teleported. The other marked tiles show useful spots to hit the respiratory systems from with a 10-range weapon.]]
[[File:Sire_in_stasis.png|thumb|200px|The Abyssal Sire in stasis.]]Overall, the optimal strategy for this phase is as follows:
#Switch to your ranged or mage gear and attack the Sire with any ranged or magic weapon/spell that is not a shadow spell to wake it up.
#Cast Shadow Barrage on the Sire to stun it. 
#Begin killing respiratory systems. Focus on killing the systems on either the east or west side, re-stun the Sire with Shadow Barrage if needed, then finish off the remaining systems.

After the last respiratory system is killed, head back to the centre and attack the Sire as soon as it steps out into the main arena (or in transit if range/mage). While damage is reduced by 50%, the amount of time the Sire takes to begin the next phase is usually significant enough to deal some damage. If the Sire somehow reaches 0 health before the next phase starts, it will begin the next phase with 40% of its health.

===Phase 2===
Stay on Row 1 during this phase, as attacking it from outside melee distance will cause the Sire to teleport you to itself and discharge a damaging blast of energy.

The Sire will use melee attacks that can hit up to 26 through prayer. Watch for miasma pools underneath the player; when they appear run to the other marked tile on Row 1. Ignore spawns unless killing the Sire at low levels with low DPS (in which case long kill times may make removing minions desirable). If reducing the Sire's defence, use one special attack now, otherwise save all special attack energy for phase 3.

Once the Sire is damaged below 50% of its health (212 health or less) it will start walking south. Run to Row 2 and activate [[Protect from Missiles]]. Advanced techniques can be used to pull the Sire south while attacking it, reducing the amount of time spent waiting for the Sire.

If the Sire reaches 0 health before the next phase starts, it will begin the next phase with 20% of its health.

===Phase 3===
====Stage I====
The Sire will latch onto the floor and summon four spawns to assist it in battle. This will occur before the pools appear. It will no longer attack with melee, but instead launch miasma pools as its "attacks". The tentacles will reawaken, limiting the amount of space allowed to attack the boss.

Once the Sire is damaged below 35% of its health (around 143 or so health), it will teleport the player, beginning the final stage.

====Stage II====
[[File:Abyssal_Sire_phase_3.gif|frame|left|The Sire opens a large portal within its body, causing spawns to emerge until it dies.]]
The Sire teleports the player to the western tile of Row 2. Two ticks later it explodes, dealing up to 96 damage if the player is within the blast radius. This damage can be recoiled with [[Vengeance]], but this requires either a spellbook switch beforehand via [[Magic cape]], [[Spellbook Swap]], or a second player to assist with [[Vengeance Other]] and [[Heal Other]]. As soon as the teleport occurs, spam-click on Row 3 to avoid the attack. Then return to melee distance to finish the fight. 

After the explosion the Sire creates a huge number of spawns. It will use its miasma pool attack a minimum of three more times, then stop as long as 15 minions are left alive. This means you should '''not''' kill any minions, but should run back and forth on Row 2 while attacking until it has made three miasma pools, after which it is safe to stop moving. Use any remaining specs and watch your health, as the scions can do a lot of damage. If the player's health drops below 40, they should run away for a brief respite.

It is possible to safespot the minions and heal off them with [[Blood Burst]]/[[Blood Barrage]]; their low magic defence should ensure all spells hit. This is primarily done for players with lower stats or are doing prolonged trips at the boss, as it is uncommon for a player even with good gear to take longer than expected or take more damage than usual from the minions. 

When the Sire is killed, all minions will die alongside it. If they were tagged by the player, this will activate [[Death Charge]], maintaining special attack energy at all times but can make trips slower due to the lack of ancients for the first phase.

