Ranged=

Ranged generally performs worse than melee, and the reduced defence will shorten trips. </br>
</br>

However, ranged can be used to deal additional damage before the start of Phase 2. Once all four respiratory systems are defeated, there is a brief window to attack the boss, despite it being out of melee range initially. Once the Abyssal Sire raises its arms, it becomes vulnerable to damage, including ranged attacks. During this window players can shoot the boss three times with the Scorching bow before it comes within melee range. Doing this can reduce its health by a good amount (up to 50% of your Scorching bow's max hit, multiplied by 3) before Phase 2 properly begins, making it a good strategy for players who want to optimize their kills.</br>
</br>
Thus, it can be a good idea to bring a few ranged switches, to ensure the player doesn't hit any zeroes while killing the respiratory systems, and to also help with the few bonus hits the Phase 1 to Phase 2 transition provides.

